00:49:33.720 --> 00:49:35.380
Tom: Why do you think having this is so universal?

00:49:35.380 --> 00:49:39.180
Why do you think people struggle with it so
much?

00:49:39.180 --> 00:49:46.970
Eric: It's really tricky because I think that
we have so many competing interests in our

00:49:46.970 --> 00:49:47.970
lives.

00:49:47.970 --> 00:49:54.220
I think a big part of it is that issue of
my book is about success, but I've talked

00:49:54.220 --> 00:50:00.891
a fair amount about happiness because we often
just conflate the two [00:50:00] and that

00:50:00.891 --> 00:50:02.480
doesn't really work.

00:50:02.480 --> 00:50:05.170
Just because somebody has a lot of money doesn't
mean they are happy.

00:50:05.170 --> 00:50:08.309
Then, just because somebody is happy doesn't
mean they have a lot of money.

00:50:08.309 --> 00:50:14.040
Obviously, we often get this feeling like
if we get power, then that will relate to

00:50:14.040 --> 00:50:17.069
happiness and that's not necessarily the case.

00:50:17.069 --> 00:50:22.499
If you look at the research by Sonja Lyubomirsky,
it showed that happiness leads to success

00:50:22.499 --> 00:50:26.720
more often than success leads to happiness.

00:50:26.720 --> 00:50:36.220
That vision [00:50:30] of power, power is
obviously for influential and helps us, especially

00:50:36.220 --> 00:50:42.049
thousand years ago helped us live longer lives,
but power is very different from like ability,

00:50:42.049 --> 00:50:43.960
from connecting with others.

00:50:43.960 --> 00:50:49.289
In fact, there's this balance where the more
powerful we feel, often we tend to dehumanize

00:50:49.289 --> 00:50:50.289
others.

00:50:50.289 --> 00:50:51.310
Empathy levels decreased.

00:50:51.310 --> 00:51:00.510
Now, power affords great things in life, level
of safety, comfort, but [00:51:00] like ability

00:51:00.510 --> 00:51:05.309
is the thing that is most correlated with
happiness, with connecting with others.

00:51:05.309 --> 00:51:08.759
When you look at longitudinal studies that
follow people their entire lives like the

00:51:08.759 --> 00:51:14.720
Grant study and the Terman study, it turns
out across the board that relationships are

00:51:14.720 --> 00:51:18.509
what brings us the most happiness, brings
most lives.

00:51:18.509 --> 00:51:21.050
Power is not connected with greatness.

00:51:21.050 --> 00:51:25.170
It's connected with having relationships because
people want stuff from you, but not with great

00:51:25.170 --> 00:51:26.170
relationships.

00:51:26.170 --> 00:51:31.180
I think we often conflate the two that very
often, [00:51:30] especially when it comes

00:51:31.180 --> 00:51:35.240
to the issue of work-life balance, we use
what's called the collapsing metric where

00:51:35.240 --> 00:51:37.280
it's just simpler if we can just track one
thing.

00:51:37.280 --> 00:51:40.559
If I can just track that one thing and I can
make that number go up, everything will be

00:51:40.559 --> 00:51:41.559
good in life.

00:51:41.559 --> 00:51:42.559
You know what?

00:51:42.559 --> 00:51:44.390
Money is a pretty easy number.

00:51:44.390 --> 00:51:48.230
People often think, "If I could just make
that number go up, everything will work out."

00:51:48.230 --> 00:51:53.910
Whereas in many cases, it actually turns out
to be the reverse in the sense that chasing

00:51:53.910 --> 00:51:56.089
money means devoting your time to work.

00:51:56.089 --> 00:52:00.230
Devoting your time to work usually means taking
your time away from relationships [00:52:00]

00:52:00.230 --> 00:52:05.990
and relationships are the things that are
most connected with meaning in life and happiness.

00:52:05.990 --> 00:52:08.170
It needs to be a balance.

00:52:08.170 --> 00:52:10.920
Tom: One of your blog articles I found this
